# set-story-llm.word — a being sets the STORY-level llm configuration on the place root
# (llm-assigner/ops.js set-story-llm DO op). MULTI-MOMENT composite (the writeLlmFields fan-out,
# now words): the 7-step chain fields each land as their OWN do:set-space fact on the story-root
# space reel — one moment per field, exactly as the old handler's per-field doVerb loop.
#
# WORD-SOLE (handler-less, Tabor's no-mirror law): this `.word` is the ONLY path (do.js
# runOpWordToStore runs it via runWordToStore; runAsStore). The host see resolve-llm-config (mode
# "story") is the floor — it runs the HEAVEN-AUTHORITY gate (hasHeavenAuthority(caller), FORBIDDEN
# otherwise), resolves the story place root (findRoot), legacy-normalizes (default slot "default"),
# runs the force-flag mutex, validates the slot, and BUILDS the { field, value } write list. It lays
# NO fact; the deeds lay the facts. ONE floor read covers the auth + the root resolve + the writes.
#
# The bridge binds `target`, `params` (the chain fields), `caller`, `branch`.

When a being sets the story-level llm configuration:
  If no caller, refuse with "set-story-llm requires an authenticated being." as unauthorized.
  see resolve-llm-config(params, caller) as cfg.
  For each w in cfg's writes:
    do set-space on the space $cfg.targetId with { field: $w.field, value: $w.value, merge: false } as wrote.
  Return spaceId: $cfg.targetId.
